# Machine Context

- This is Jack's personal i3/Xorg workstation.
- Dotfiles live in `/home/jackmhny/dotfiles`.
- Development workspaces live in `/home/jackmhny/dev`.
- User systemd units live in `/home/jackmhny/.config/systemd/user`.

## Sudo On This Machine

Fingerprint auth works globally from the desktop session. For narrow admin actions, send a one-sentence dunst notification, then run normal `sudo` and let Jack press the fingerprint reader.

```sh
dunstify -u normal -t 10000 "Agent sudo request" "<one sentence reason>" 2>/dev/null || true
sudo <command>
```

If fingerprint auth times out, say that and rerun the same narrow command once Jack is ready.
